Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Trim the @butternut squash{1}, halve lengthways, then scoop out the seeds (peel first if you prefer). Cut into small 1cm chunks - you want them small so they cook faster. Pop onto a large #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf of the oven until golden and tender, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

While the squash roasts, bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the linguine.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced). Cut the @Tenderstem® broccoli{80%g} in half widthways. Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Roughly tear the @Serrano ham{6%slices} into large pieces.

When your pan of water is boiling, add the @linguine{180%g} and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, reserve some of the pasta water, then drain in a #colander{} and pop back into the pan.

Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

While your pasta cooks, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

When hot, lay the Serrano ham in the pan and fry until crisp, ~{2-3%minutes} each side, then transfer to a #plate{} covered in #kitchen paper{} and set aside.

Add a drizzle more @oil{} to the pan, then add the onion. Stir-fry until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add the broccoli and stir-fry for ~{2-3%minutes}, then add a splash of water. Pop a lid on the pan or cover in #foil{} and cook until tender, another ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once the broccoli is tender, remove the lid, stir in the garlic and cook for ~{30%seconds}.

Pour the @reserved pasta water{125%ml} and @chicken stock paste{10%g} into the pan, then stir in the @creme fraiche{150%g} and Serrano ham.

Bring to the boil, then remove from the heat.

Add the cooked pasta and roasted butternut squash to the sauce.

Taste and add salt and pepper if needed. Add a splash of @water{} if it's a little thick.

Toss gently to coat, then serve your linguine in large #bowls{}.

Enjoy!